<Review ID>3702171
<Product Name>Creative Zen 4 GB MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>Returned iPod Nano to buy Creative Zen
<Date>Fri Nov 30 00:00:00 CST 2007
<Content>I listen to music when running on the treadmill. I returned my iPod nano to get this Creative product for various reasons:  1) I needed FM radio for my treadmill workouts which the iPod nano lacks. Let the Radio DJs shuffle the latest and greatest songs for me!  2) During workouts, I prefer the sturdy build of Zen over iPod nano's handle-me-with-care body.  3) Can listen to music and watch my picture slideshows at the same time. This is not possible with iPod nano.  3) User interface is great! Smooth fonts, nice graphics & easy navigation. Almost as good as iPod nano.  4) I use SD cards to store and play more music. This isn't possible with iPod nano.  5) The jpeg images are stored as is and a nice thumbnail gallery is displayed. Images are crystal clear when viewed using Zen. In contrast, iPod nano doesn't store images as individual files. Your images tend to take more space on iPod nano.  6) PC Software that comes with the player is okay.  7) Earphone that comes with the player is average. Buy Koss sportapro for your jogging needs.   8) Short USB cable is cute.  I highly recommend this mp3 player for your workout needs. If you are an audiophile, research other players before choosing Creative Zen.  
<Overall>4

