<Product Name>Creative Zen 4 GB MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>Great MP3, Just Needs Better Volume
<Date>Thu Jan 24 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>I've always been a fan of the Zen and Creative Labs products.  I'm glad that this mp3 is small enough to fit in my wallet and can play movies downloaded from Amazon and Walmart (well not Walmart anymore - which was disappointing).  I'm anxious to see if I can purchase movies from ITune and play them on my zen.  The 4GB was a good first MP3 for my 13 year old son.  He was excited because he knows he can use a SD card for additional storage.  As for me, I was excited to see the 32GB was finally in stock at Creative Labs.  I have so much music and I'm not one to be transporting several SD Cards - one will be enough).  My only complaint is that the volume does not get that loud.  It's not as loud as the buckier Zen I have and I compared it to the volume of a friend's IPOD and it wasn't that great. There was a problem that the firmware corrected where the Zen 4, 8 and 16 GB players would only play the first song of an album and with 4 seconds left it would stop playing.  You would then need to manually make the player go to the next song.  I spoke to customer service at Creative Lab and they told me to download the latest firmware.  It corrected this issue and I was very happy. I'm looking forward to Creative Lab coming out with a portable docking station with speakers for the Zen like they have for IPOD.   
