<Review ID>5696925
<Product Name>Creative Zen 4 GB MP3 Player (Black)
<Title>Creative outdoes themselves
<Date>Wed Jan 23 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>I got this for my wife and I have to say that I was tempted to keep it for myself...or at least get my own.  Don't get me wrong, my Zune is great, but Creative have really outdone themselves this time around. So much to the point that I'm thinking of switching over.   In the past I owned a Zen Microphoto and loved it. I ended up passing it down to my brother and it's really taken some hard use and abuse and still works perfectly. I never thought they would top that player and to tell you the truth, I've always kinda regretted letting it go.      When I got wind of this player, late last Summer, I just couldn't wait to see what they had done this time out. I was really intrigued by the size and the very fact that it would be replacing the Zen Vision M.  That was another amazing player so my expectations just grew and grew. Like I was saying, this model is replacing the hard-drive Zen Vision M altogether with several different models (4,8, and 16 gig) of the new flash based Zen. As soon as you get it out of the box, the first thing you will notice is how solid it feels in your hand and how it's just the right size. Once you get the software up and going (seemless) and get some tracks on it, you will be amazed at the sound quality that comes through the included earbuds. (as with all other Creative players, you really don't even have to install the software if you don't want too.) It also seems like they've packed this player with every feature imaginable.  There's an equalizer, a voice recorder, am/fm tuner, and most importantly, there's a SD slot for memory expansion which should be a big selling-point for many.  Awesome.  The video playback on the 2.5 inch screen is gorgeous and the ability to store album art is a big plus.  Oh, and I love the interface.  Needless to say, this was a gift that was kinda tough to give.   Seriously, I can't think one single complaint with this player. I know I'll soon be getting one for myself. You're  really getting a lot for your money here.  If the nano just doesn't do it for you, then you may want to consider the Zen.  It's a way better value, and anyway you cut it, it really beats having to mess with itunes.      
<Overall>5

